cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.PF

This paper focuses on the evaluation of high-speed TCP variants over high-BDP networks using network simulation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the advantages and disadvantages of different TCP variants in terms of throughput, loss-ratio, and fairness, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of TCP variants, which could be related to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.PF (Performance).
